/**
34 
 * <p>Operations on {@link java.lang.String} that are
35 
 * {@code null} safe.</p>
36 
 *
37 
 * <ul>
38 
 *  <li><b>IsEmpty/IsBlank</b>
39 
 *      - checks if a String contains text</li>
40 
 *  <li><b>Trim/Strip</b>
41 
 *      - removes leading and trailing whitespace</li>
42 
 *  <li><b>Equals/Compare</b>
43 
 *      - compares two strings in a null-safe manner</li>
44 
 *  <li><b>startsWith</b>
45 
 *      - check if a String starts with a prefix in a null-safe manner</li>
46 
 *  <li><b>endsWith</b>
47 
 *      - check if a String ends with a suffix in a null-safe manner</li>
48 
 *  <li><b>IndexOf/LastIndexOf/Contains</b>
49 
 *      - null-safe index-of checks
50 
 *  <li><b>IndexOfAny/LastIndexOfAny/IndexOfAnyBut/LastIndexOfAnyBut</b>
51 
 *      - index-of any of a set of Strings</li>
52 
 *  <li><b>ContainsOnly/ContainsNone/ContainsAny</b>
53 
 *      - checks if String contains only/none/any of these characters</li>
54 
 *  <li><b>Substring/Left/Right/Mid</b>
55 
 *      - null-safe substring extractions</li>
56 
 *  <li><b>SubstringBefore/SubstringAfter/SubstringBetween</b>
57 
 *      - substring extraction relative to other strings</li>
58 
 *  <li><b>Split/Join</b>
59 
 *      - splits a String into an array of substrings and vice versa</li>
60 
 *  <li><b>Remove/Delete</b>
61 
 *      - removes part of a String</li>
62 
 *  <li><b>Replace/Overlay</b>
63 
 *      - Searches a String and replaces one String with another</li>
64 
 *  <li><b>Chomp/Chop</b>
65 
 *      - removes the last part of a String</li>
66 
 *  <li><b>AppendIfMissing</b>
67 
 *      - appends a suffix to the end of the String if not present</li>
68 
 *  <li><b>PrependIfMissing</b>
69 
 *      - prepends a prefix to the start of the String if not present</li>
70 
 *  <li><b>LeftPad/RightPad/Center/Repeat</b>
71 
 *      - pads a String</li>
72 
 *  <li><b>UpperCase/LowerCase/SwapCase/Capitalize/Uncapitalize</b>
73 
 *      - changes the case of a String</li>
74 
 *  <li><b>CountMatches</b>
75 
 *      - counts the number of occurrences of one String in another</li>
76 
 *  <li><b>IsAlpha/IsNumeric/IsWhitespace/IsAsciiPrintable</b>
77 
 *      - checks the characters in a String</li>
78 
 *  <li><b>DefaultString</b>
79 
 *      - protects against a null input String</li>
80 
 *  <li><b>Rotate</b>
81 
 *      - rotate (circular shift) a String</li>
82 
 *  <li><b>Reverse/ReverseDelimited</b>
83 
 *      - reverses a String</li>
84 
 *  <li><b>Abbreviate</b>
85 
 *      - abbreviates a string using ellipses or another given String</li>
86 
 *  <li><b>Difference</b>
87 
 *      - compares Strings and reports on their differences</li>
88 
 *  <li><b>LevenshteinDistance</b>
89 
 *      - the number of changes needed to change one String into another</li>
90 
 * </ul>
91 
 *
92 
 * <p>The {@code StringUtils} class defines certain words related to
93 
 * String handling.</p>
94 
 *
95 
 * <ul>
96 
 *  <li>null - {@code null}</li>
97 
 *  <li>empty - a zero-length string ({@code ""})</li>
98 
 *  <li>space - the space character ({@code ' '}, char 32)</li>
99 
 *  <li>whitespace - the characters defined by {@link Character#isWhitespace(char)}</li>
100 
 *  <li>trim - the characters &lt;= 32 as in {@link String#trim()}</li>
101 
 * </ul>
102 
 *
103 
 * <p>{@code StringUtils} handles {@code null} input Strings quietly.
104 
 * That is to say that a {@code null} input will return {@code null}.
105 
 * Where a {@code boolean} or {@code int} is being returned
106 
 * details vary by method.</p>
107 
 *
108 
 * <p>A side effect of the {@code null} handling is that a
109 
 * {@code NullPointerException} should be considered a bug in
110 
 * {@code StringUtils}.</p>
111 
 *
112 
 * <p>Methods in this class include sample code in their Javadoc comments to explain their operation.
113 
 * The symbol {@code *} is used to indicate any input including {@code null}.</p>
114 
 *
115 
 * <p>#ThreadSafe#</p>
116 
 * @see java.lang.String
117 
 * @since 1.0
118 
 */
119 
//@Immutable
120 
public class StringUtils {
121
122 
    private static final int STRING_BUILDER_SIZE = 256;
123
124 
    // Performance testing notes (JDK 1.4, Jul03, scolebourne)
125 
    // Whitespace:
126 
    // Character.isWhitespace() is faster than WHITESPACE.indexOf()
127 
    // where WHITESPACE is a string of all whitespace characters
128 
    //
129 
    // Character access:
130 
    // String.charAt(n) versus toCharArray(), then array[n]
131 
    // String.charAt(n) is about 15% worse for a 10K string
132 
    // They are about equal for a length 50 string
133 
    // String.charAt(n) is about 4 times better for a length 3 string
134 
    // String.charAt(n) is best bet overall
135 
    //
136 
    // Append:
137 
    // String.concat about twice as fast as StringBuffer.append
138 
    // (not sure who tested this)
139

    /**
190 
     * <p>Abbreviates a String using ellipses. This will turn
191 
     * "Now is the time for all good men" into "Now is the time for..."</p>
192 
     *
193 
     * <p>Specifically:</p>
194 
     * <ul>
195 
     *   <li>If the number of characters in {@code str} is less than or equal to
196 
     *       {@code maxWidth}, return {@code str}.</li>
197 
     *   <li>Else abbreviate it to {@code (substring(str, 0, max-3) + "...")}.</li>
198 
     *   <li>If {@code maxWidth} is less than {@code 4}, throw an
199 
     *       {@code IllegalArgumentException}.</li>
200 
     *   <li>In no case will it return a String of length greater than
201 
     *       {@code maxWidth}.</li>
202 
     * </ul>
203 
     *
204 
     * <pre>
205 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate(null, *)      = null
206 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("", 4)        = ""
207 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", 6) = "abc..."
208 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", 7) = "abcdefg"
209 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", 8) = "abcdefg"
210 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", 4) = "a..."
211 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", 3) = IllegalArgumentException
212 
     * </pre>
213 
     *
214 
     * @param str  the String to check, may be null
215 
     * @param maxWidth  maximum length of result String, must be at least 4
216 
     * @return abbreviated String, {@code null} if null String input
217 
     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the width is too small
218 
     * @since 2.0
219 
     */
220 
    public static String abbreviate(final String str, final int maxWidth) {

    }

    /**
225 
     * <p>Abbreviates a String using ellipses. This will turn
226

227

228

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefghijklmno", 5, 10)  = "...fghi..."

245 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefghijklmno", 8, 10)  = "...ijklmno"
246 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefghijklmno", 10, 10) = "...ijklmno"
247 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefghijklmno", 12, 10) = "...ijklmno"

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefghij", 0, 3)        = IllegalArgumentException

    /**

     * "Now is the time for all good men" into "Now is the time for..." if "..." was defined

     *   <li>Else abbreviate it to {@code (substring(str, 0, max-abbrevMarker.length) + abbrevMarker)}.</li>

     *   <li>If {@code maxWidth} is less than {@code abbrevMarker.length + 1}, throw an

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("", "...", 4)        = ""

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", ".", 5)   = "abcd."

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", ".", 7)   = "abcdefg"
285 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", ".", 8)   = "abcdefg"
286 
     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", "..", 4)  = "ab.."
287

     * StringUtils.abbreviate("abcdefg", "..", 2)  = IllegalArgumentException

290 
     * </pre>
291 
     *
292 
     * @param str  the String to check, may be null
293 
     * @param abbrevMarker  the String used as replacement marker
294 
     * @param maxWidth  maximum length of result String, must be at least {@code abbrevMarker.length + 1}
295 
     * @return abbreviated String, {@code null} if null String input

     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the width is too small
297 
     * @since 3.6

    /**
374 
     * <p>Abbreviates a String to the length passed, replacing the middle characters with the supplied
375 
     * replacement String.</p>
376 
     *
377 
     * <p>This abbreviation only occurs if the following criteria is met:</p>
378 
     * <ul>
379 
     * <li>Neither the String for abbreviation nor the replacement String are null or empty </li>
380 
     * <li>The length to truncate to is less than the length of the supplied String</li>
381 
     * <li>The length to truncate to is greater than 0</li>
382 
     * <li>The abbreviated String will have enough room for the length supplied replacement String
383 
     * and the first and last characters of the supplied String for abbreviation</li>

     * StringUtils.abbreviateMiddle("abc", ".", 0)      = "abc"

     * StringUtils.abbreviateMiddle("abc", ".", 3)      = "abc"
393 
     * StringUtils.abbreviateMiddle("abcdef", ".", 4)     = "ab.f"
